Specific_Instance_Per_Administrative_Are.Annotation: CNN Center was severely damaged, including shattered windows and damage to the glass roof of the atrium which caused flooding in part of the food court.

The Omni Hotel, particularly its skywalk between the two hotel towers over Andrew Young International Boulevard, was damaged; the complex lost 476 windows, forcing the closure of the south tower.
The Georgia Dome had its facade damaged; panels were ripped from the exterior and two holes were torn in the roof during a basketball game.
A Philips Arena parking garage sustained damage to its facade while hosting basketball games.
Two of the giant columns in Centennial Olympic Park were knocked down.
The Ritz Carlton had windows blown out.
The Westin Peachtree Plaza experienced blown-out windows, with continued window fallout forcing pedestrian closures around nearby areas and stations.
The Georgia-Pacific Building had windows blown out.
SunTrust Plaza had windows blown out; more than 60 people had to be relocated from their offices there.
The Equitable Building suffered blown-out windows, with a reported 300 windows affected.
Georgia State University had windows blown out.
The historic Rialto Theatre at GSU sustained roof damage which led to water damage inside.
Grady Hospital reported damage to windows along with a power outage.
The King Memorial MARTA station was damaged, leading to trains bypassing it and bus reroutes.
Oakland Cemetery suffered major damage to its monuments and trees, with window blinds even found wrapped around a statue.
A brick loft building in the Cabbagetown area lost part of its roof and a portion of its top (fifth) floor.
Another building at The Stacks on Boulevard was damaged; search and rescue personnel were unable to enter, though everyone was accounted for.
At the nearby Philips Arena, damage occurred to the exterior of the arena during a basketball game.
